@pdpinch 
<img width="1205" alt="screen shot 2017-02-27 at 6 19 35 pm" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/10431250/23362809/51c92da4-fd19-11e6-85eb-9b797b1c7c1e.png">

This is effectively re-opening #1449 due to an error that was discovered on release candidate 0.21.0

The logic to display "no results" messages to users on the search results page seems to be faulty. Here's a code snippet on the release-candidate branch:

```javascript
renderFacets: Function = (currentProgramEnrollment: ProgramEnrollment): React$Element<*> => {
    if (_.isNull(this.getResults())) {
      return (
        <Card className="fullwidth" shadow={1}>
          <div className="no-hits left-nav">
            {`There are no users in the ${currentProgramEnrollment.title} program.`}
          </div>
        </Card>
      );
    }
```

Here's a screenshot of some `console.log` lines I put into `renderFacets` to debug this:

![ss 2016-11-04 at 11 28 40](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/14932219/20011413/f70f92aa-a281-11e6-9e3b-4a1c663e8868.png)

`this.getResults()` is not returning `null`. It's returning an object with no hits.

from dashboard/api.py:265

``` python
    if course_enrollment.is_verified:
        if course_run.is_current:
            status = CourseRunStatus.CURRENTLY_ENROLLED
        elif course_run.is_past:
            status = CourseRunStatus.READ_CERT
        elif course_run.is_future:
            status = CourseRunStatus.WILL_ATTEND
    else:
        if (course_run.is_current or course_run.is_future) and course_run.is_upgradable:
            status = CourseRunStatus.CAN_UPGRADE
        else:
            status = CourseRunStatus.NOT_PASSED
```

If an unverified course run is current/future, but not upgradable, we are assigning a status that indicates that it is a failed course run

from static/js/components/dashboard/CourseDescription.js

``` javascript
case STATUS_NOT_PASSED:
      if (firstRun.course_end_date) {
        let courseEndDate = moment(firstRun.course_end_date);
        return this.courseDate('Ended', courseEndDate);
      } else if (!_.isNil(firstRun.fuzzy_start_date)) {
        return `Coming ${firstRun.fuzzy_start_date}`;
      }
      break;
```

the `else if` conditional does not make sense here. if a course has the status `NOT_PASSED`, it happened in the past by definition. whether or not this conditional can be reached under normal circumstances, it's clearly misplaced, and it's very possible that it should be shown for a different course run status
